titlestmt.titleproper: A Guide to the Rockefeller Foundation records, Biographical File FA485

profiledesc.creation: This finding aid was produced using ArchivesSpace on 2021-01-29 00:09:30 -0500.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The Rockefeller Foundation Biographical File is arranged alphabetically by the last name/family name of the individual or by institutional name.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Open for research. Brittle or damaged items are available at the discretion of RAC. Researchers interested in accessing digital media (floppy disks, CDs, DVDs, etc.) or audiovisual material (audio cassettes, VHS, etc.) in this collection must use an access surrogate. The original items may not be accessed because of preservation concerns. To request an access surrogate be made, or if you are unsure if there is an access surrogate, please contact an archivist.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The scope and breadth of the Biographical File is inconsistent. Some files are rich, while others are sparse.

Individual files may contain: biographical sketches, curriculum vitaes and resumes, obituaries, press releases, photographs, articles and publications. Files may also document honors, awards, appointments and positions held.
